Title:	  Design document for PDMget_dyn_upd_attr function
Author:   Audra Romans
Date:     9/8/93
Revision: 2


Abstract:
	
	This function returns an attribute buffer and a data buffer
        to be used during retrieval of attributes for place part.
        The attribute buffer will consist of attribute num, attribute
        name, synonym and data type. The data buffer will consist of the 
        default value for the attribute. This function will be called by
        PDMquery_dynamic_attributes.

Function Protocol:

PDMget_dyn_upd_attr(dyn_tab_no,attr_buff,data_buff)
int dyn_tab_no
MEMptr *attr_buff
MEMptr *data_buff

Inputs:
	
	dyn_tab_no - table no for dynamic table
                     required
Outputs:

	attr_buff  - a pointer to the attribute information for the
        catalog, part number and revision loaded in the PDMexec structure.

        data_buff - a pointer to the default value information for the
        catalog, part number and revision loaded in the PDMexec structure.
        

Assumptions:

	PDMquery_dynamic_attr will receive a null buffer for the list_buffer.

Return Status:

	PDM_S_SUCCESS
        sql error messages

Algorithm:

	
        query nfmattribute for n_attrno, n_name, n_datatype, n_synonym, 
        n_null  where (n_tableno = dyn_tab_no) and (n_write = 'Y')
        if (status != PDM_S_SUCCESS)
           return(status)

        assign *attr_bufr to attr_list

        query nfmvalues for n_defaultvalue, n_listno, n_maxvalue, n_minvalue 
        given n_attrno
        if (status != PDM_S_SUCCESS)
          return(status)

        assign *data_bufr to data_list

 	return(PDM_S_SUCCESS)

